.TH "sba_map_single" 9 "sba_map_single" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sba_map_single \- map one buffer and return IOVA for DMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "dma_addr_t" sba_map_single
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "void *addr "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction direction "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
instance of PCI owned by the driver that's asking.
.IP "addr" 12
driver buffer to map.
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to map in driver buffer.
.IP "direction" 12
R/W or both.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
See Documentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst
